<subSubSection id="C35D6502FFF6FFE08592FBA7FD321D11" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF83689FFF6FFE08592FBA7FD321D11" blockId="4.[151,761,959,1718]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE08592FBA7FE421F11" bold="true" box="[151,392,1087,1110]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C474D0AFFF6FFE0848BFBA7FDDD1F11" authority="Kundrata &amp; Sormova, 2018" authorityName="Kundrata &amp; Sormova" authorityYear="2018" box="[398,535,1087,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Selasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jenisi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE0848BFBA7FDDD1F11" box="[398,535,1087,1110]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Selasia jenisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20057E0FFF6FFE08718FBA7FDA71F11" box="[541,621,1087,1110]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D0AFFF6FFE08464FBC7FD7B1F31" authority="Kundrata, 2017" authorityName="Kundrata" authorityYear="2017" box="[353,689,1119,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Selasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrobrunnea">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE08464FBC7FDC21F31" box="[353,520,1119,1142]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">S. nigrobrunnea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD64B78FFF6FFE0870AFBC7FD7B1F31" author="KUNDRATA R." box="[527,689,1119,1142]" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" pagination="380 - 386" part="4344" refId="ref4466" refString="KUNDRATA R. 2017: New species of Selasia Laporte, 1836 (Elateridae: Agrypninae: Drilini) from Nepal and Pakistan. Zootaxa 4344: 380 - 386." title="New species of Selasia Laporte, 1836 (Elateridae: Agrypninae: Drilini) from Nepal and Pakistan" type="journal article" year="2017">Kundrata, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D0AFFF6FFE087E1FBC7FEAE1FD1" authority="Pic, 1914" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Selasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atriventris">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE087E1FBC7FECB1FD1" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">S. atriventris</emphasis>
Pic, 1914
</taxonomicName>
(both also from 
<collectingCountry id="F3507619FFF6FFE08703FBE7FD8F1FD1" box="[518,581,1151,1174]" name="Nepal" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Nepal</collectingCountry>
) by its characteristically robust habitus and body coloration (
<taxonomicName id="4C474D0AFFF6FFE08757FB07FD3D1FF1" authorityName="Kundrata" authorityYear="2017" box="[594,759,1183,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Selasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrobrunnea">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE08757FB07FD3D1FF1" box="[594,759,1183,1206]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">S. nigrobrunnea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the pronotum distinctly darker than remaining body parts, 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D0AFFF6FFE085DDFB47FE951FB1" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1914" box="[216,351,1247,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Selasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atriventris">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE085DDFB47FE951FB1" box="[216,351,1247,1270]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">S. atriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the whole body light-colored, i.e., yellowish brown to brown). The new species shares similar body coloration (i.e., the antennal branches and elytra darker than remaining body parts) with 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D0AFFF6FFE084D8FAA7FD321E11" authority="Kundrata, 2012" authorityName="Kundrata" authorityYear="2012" box="[477,760,1343,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Selasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boruckae">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE084D8FAA7FD9F1E11" box="[477,597,1343,1366]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">S. boruckae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD64B78FFF6FFE0875CFAA7FD321E11" author="KUNDRATA R." box="[601,760,1343,1366]" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" pagination="261 - 266" part="62" refId="ref4384" refString="KUNDRATA R. 2012 a: Taxonomic review of the Himalayan species of Selasia Laporte, 1836 (Coleoptera: Elateridae: Agrypninae: Drilini). Annales Zoologici 62: 261 - 266." title="Taxonomic review of the Himalayan species of Selasia Laporte, 1836 (Coleoptera: Elateridae: Agrypninae: Drilini)" type="journal article" year="2012">Kundrata, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from central 
<collectingCountry id="F3507619FFF6FFE0841BFAC7FE951E31" box="[286,351,1375,1398]" name="Nepal" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Nepal</collectingCountry>
. The latter species differs in having the body narrower with relatively long elytra which are usually more than 4.50 times as long as pronotum (3.85 times in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D0AFFF6FFE087E1FA07FF041E91" authority="Kundrata &amp; Sormova, 2018" authorityName="Kundrata &amp; Sormova" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Selasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jenisi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE087E1FA07FF041E91" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">S. jenisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20057E0FFF6FFE085D6FA27FEE91E91" box="[211,291,1471,1494]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), relatively small eyes with their frontal distance 1.65–1.80 times eye diameter (1.45 times in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D0AFFF6FFE08787FA47FD1E1EB1" authority="Kundrata &amp; Sormova, 2018" authorityName="Kundrata &amp; Sormova" authorityYear="2018" box="[642,724,1503,1526]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Selasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jenisi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE08787FA47FD1E1EB1" box="[642,724,1503,1526]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">S. jenisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20057E0FFF6FFE087DFFA47FF0F1D51" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), distinctly diverging posterior angles of pronotum (short and subrectangular in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D0AFFF6FFE0847EF987FE071D71" authority="Kundrata &amp; Sormova, 2018" authorityName="Kundrata &amp; Sormova" authorityYear="2018" box="[379,461,1567,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Selasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jenisi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE0847EF987FE071D71" box="[379,461,1567,1590]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">S. jenisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20057E0FFF6FFE084D6F987FDEC1D71" box="[467,550,1567,1590]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), and the phallobase longer than wide (about as long as wide in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D0AFFF6FFE08743F9A7FD5C1D11" authority="Kundrata &amp; Sormova, 2018" authorityName="Kundrata &amp; Sormova" authorityYear="2018" box="[582,662,1599,1622]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Selasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jenisi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE08743F9A7FD5C1D11" box="[582,662,1599,1622]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">S. jenisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20057E0FFF6FFE0879EF9A7FD271D11" box="[667,749,1599,1622]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35D6502FFF6FFE08592F9C7FE351DD1" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF83689FFF6FFE08592F9C7FE351DD1" blockId="4.[151,761,959,1718]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">
<emphasis id="B933EA9BFFF6FFE08592F9C7FEDE1D31" bold="true" box="[151,276,1631,1654]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a patronym in honor of Ivo Jeniš (Lutín, 
<collectingCountry id="F3507619FFF6FFE0844CF9E7FE391DD1" box="[329,499,1663,1686]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
